      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;not-prose&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/fake-http.jpg&#34;&#xA;      alt=&#34;Fake HTTP&#34; &#xA;      loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In Laravel, one of the powerful tools for testing is the ability to simulate HTTP responses without actually hitting an external API. This is particularly useful when you need to ensure your application behaves correctly regardless of the API&amp;rsquo;s response.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
